cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.SE 

This paper is primarily focused on network security and preventing denial of service attacks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). It also involves cryptography and secure communication (cs.CR), as well as distributed systems and algorithms (cs.DC) for managing network congestion. The use of feedback mechanisms and fair resource allocation also relates to control systems (cs.SY) and software engineering (cs.SE).
